[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Skip the fishing minigame entirely, with knobs for everything else: spawn rate, bobber range, rare-fish odds, museum-item odds, and more.[/size]

[size=3][b]Skip the minigame[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-reel[/b] — fish are reeled in automatically. Optionally keep the reel animation if you want the visual; turn it off for fully silent fishing.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Tune the minigame instead[/b] — if you'd rather not skip it outright, adjust minigame speed and the win-area size to make it trivial without removing it.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Recommended Settings button[/b] — one click in the config menu applies a known-good baseline.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Spawn &amp; rarity[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Spawn rate &amp; population[/b] — control how often fish spawn and the cap on how many can be present in a body of water.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Rare-fish odds[/b] — multiplier on the odds of pulling rarer species.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Museum-item odds[/b] — separate multiplier for museum items, since they share the fishing loot table.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Bobber &amp; rod[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Instant attraction[/b] — fish head straight for the bobber the moment it lands.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Bigger bobber radius[/b] — wider area of attraction so casts don't have to be precise.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Faster swim speed[/b] — fish reach the bobber faster.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Casting speed &amp; throw distance[/b] — adjust rod cast speed and how far the bobber travels per throw.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Bubble Net capacity[/b] — customise how many fish the Bubble Net spell catches in one go.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Quiet mode[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Disable "You caught a fish!" popup[/b] — no more pop-up every catch when you're churning through fish.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/222]No Time To Stop &amp; Eat[/url] — same idea applied to eating: instant effect, no pause.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/37]Easy Living[/url] — broader QoL grab-bag; quick-save and auto-load go nicely with hands-off fishing.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/199]Auto Tools[/url] — automatic tool-swap means you can switch from fishing to farming and back without scrolling the action bar.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31]Keep Alive[/url] — required by this mod; keeps everything loaded between play sessions.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30][size=3]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/size][/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31][size=3]Keep Alive[/size][/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[size=3]Built and tested against the latest Steam build of Sun Haven.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Sun Haven&#92;BepInEx&#92;plugins[/code][/size]

